            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-10-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-10-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="247" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Harvey</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 152.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-10-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 31, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch of the 1st instant, No. 294, has
                    been received, and I commend the promptness with which you used the means at
                    your disposal for having a proper watch kept upon the movements of the
                    suspicious steamer to which you refer as having been seen off the coast of
                    Sicily.</p>
                <p>Your communication has been submitted for perusal to the Secretary of the
                    Navy.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Lisbon.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
